{"lemma": "أَحِبَّةً", "slug": "أَحِبَّةً", "root": "ح.ب.ب", "root_slug": "ح-ب-ب", "root_link": "/words/roots/ح-ب-ب", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["adj", "noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 7}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n6842"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8B"}}, "translations": {"en": "beloved", "fa": "دوست‌داشتنی", "ur": "محبوب", "tr": "sevimli", "id": "kesayangan", "bn": "প্রিয়", "es": "amado", "fr": "bien-aimé", "de": "geliebt", "ru": "возлюбленный", "zh": "挚爱"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "adj", "gloss": "beloved"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "agreeable"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "beloved", "examples": [{"text": "وَقَالَتِ ٱلْيَهُودُ وَٱلنَّصَارَى نَحْنُ أَبْنَاءُ ٱللّٰهِ وَأَحِبَّاؤُهُ قُلْ فَلِمَ يُعَذِّبُكُم بِذُنُوبِكُم بَلْ أَنْتُم بَشَرٌ مِمَّنْ خَلَقَ يَغْفِرُ لِمَن يَشَاءُ وَيُعَذِّبُ مَن يَشَاءُ وَلِلّٰهِ مُلْكُ ٱلسَّمَاوَاتِ وَٱلْأَرْضِ وَمَا بَيْنَهُمَا وَإِلَيْهِ ٱلْمَصِيرُ", "english": "But the Jews and the Christians say, \"We are the children of Allah and His beloved.\" Say, \"Then why does He punish you for your sins?\" Rather, you are human beings from among those He has created. He forgives whom He wills, and He punishes whom He wills. And to Allah belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them, and to Him is the [final] destination."}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "sweetheart"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "dear"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "darling", "examples": [{"text": "يَا حَبِيبِي!", "english": "oh my darling!"}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "frequently used title of God, the Beloved, the Focus of one's heart and devotion"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "From the root ح ب ب (ḥ b b). Compare Hebrew חָבִיב (ḥāḇīḇ), Classical Syriac ܚܒܝܒܐ (ḥabbīḇā)."}, "ipa": ["/ħa.biːb/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n6842", "headword_ar": "احبّهُ", "root": "Hb", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, A, Msb, K,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHobaAbN", "text_ar": "اـِحْبَابٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (KL;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hab~ahu", "text_ar": "حَبَّهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) first pers."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hababotuhu", "text_ar": "حَبَبْتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb, K,) aor."}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is anomalous, (S, Msb, K,) the regular aor. being"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is unused, (Msb,) [said to be] the only instance of a trans. verb whose second and third radical letters are the same having the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yafoEilu", "text_ar": "يَفْعِلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as that of its aor. without having also the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yafoEulu", "text_ar": "يَفْعُلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) and therefore by some disapproved, as not chaste, and disallowed by Az, though he allows the pass. form"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hub~a", "text_ar": "حُبَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hub~N", "text_ar": "حُبٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) or this is a simple subst., (Msb,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hib~N", "text_ar": "حِبٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (K;) and [↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hab~ahu", "text_ar": "حَبَّهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] first pers."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Habibotuhu", "text_ar": "حَبِبْتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAb~hu", "text_ar": "حَابّهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HibaAbN", "text_ar": "حِبَابٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", of the dial. of Hudheyl; (Msb;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AstHb~hu", "text_ar": "استحبّهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Msb, K;) signify the same; (S, Msb, K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He loved, affected, liked, approved,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "took pleasure in, him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, K, and KL in explanation of the first and last:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he held him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "esteemed him, as a friend:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(KL in explanation of the first and last:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AisotiHobaAbN", "text_ar": "اِسْتِحْبَابٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "esteeming"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[a person or thing]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "good:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S:) and the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "preferring,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "choosing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[a person or thing,] as also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iHobaAbN", "text_ar": "اـِحْبَابٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (KL:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AstHb~hu EalaY gayorihi", "text_ar": "استحبّهُ عَلَى غَيْرِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he loved,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "esteemed, him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, above another,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "others; preferred him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, to another,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "others."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, A, * TA.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA A^aHabotu *`lika", "text_ar": "مَا اَحَبْتُ ذٰلِكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the dial. of the tribe of Suleym, is for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mA A^aHobabotuhu", "text_ar": "ما اَحْبَبْتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I loved not,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "liked not, that"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Zanotu", "text_ar": "ظَنْتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Zananotu", "text_ar": "ظَنَنْتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Zalotu", "text_ar": "ظَلْتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Zilotu", "text_ar": "ظِلْتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Zalilotu", "text_ar": "ظَلِلْتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Lh, TA.) ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^uHib~u A^ano yakwuna ka*aA", "text_ar": "اُحِبُّ اَنْ يَكوُنَ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "may be rendered"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I would that it were thus,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that such a thing were."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] It is said of Ohod, in a trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa jabalN yuHib~unaA wanuHib~uhu", "text_ar": "هُوَ جَبَلٌ يُحِبُّنَا وَنُحِبُّهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It is a mountain whose inhabitants love us, and whose inhabitants we love:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or it may mean we love the mountain itself, because it is in the land of people whom we love. (IAth, TA.) And one says"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY saAEapK yuHib~uhaA", "text_ar": "فِى سَاعَةٍ يُحِبُّهَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlT~aEaAmu", "text_ar": "الطَّعَامُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yuHab~u fiyhaA", "text_ar": "يُحَبُّ فِيهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "In an hour,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a time, in which food is loved,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "liked"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA A^aHab~ahu", "text_ar": "مَا اَحَبَّهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ilaY~a", "text_ar": "اـِلَىَّ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hab~a bihi", "text_ar": "حَبَّ بِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "How beloved, lovely, pleasing, charming,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "excellent, is he,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, to me!"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (As, S, K, * TA;) and so"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHobibo A_ilaY~a bihi", "text_ar": "اَحْبِبْ اـِلَىَّ بِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (A, TA.) [De Sacy, in his Gram. Ar., sec. ed., ii. 221, mentions the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA A^aHab~a Almuw^omina ll~`hi wamaA A^aHab~ahu A_ilaY A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "مَا اَحَبَّ المُوْمِنَ للّٰهِ وَمَا اَحَبَّهُ اـِلَى ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "How greatly does the believer love God! and how great an object of love is he to God!"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AHb~", "text_ar": "احبّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K,) inf. n. as above, (S,) also signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a camel)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "kneeled and lay down, and would not spring up:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "was restive:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "kneeled and lay down:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "was afflicted by a fracture,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "disease, and would not move from his place until cured,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "remained there until he died:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AZ, S, K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became jaded:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA: [agreeably with this last explanation the act. part. n. is rendered in the S and K on the authority of Th:]) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "was at the point of death,"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 496}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by reason of violent disease, and therefore kneeled and lay down, and could not be roused."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AHeyth, TA.) Accord. to AO,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHobabotu Hub~a Alxayori Eano *ikori", "text_ar": "اَحْبَبْتُ حُبَّ الخَيْرِ عَنْ ذِكْرِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rab~iY", "text_ar": "رَبِّى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in the Kur xxxviii. 31] means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I have stuck to the ground, on account of my love of the horses,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[lit.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of good things,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and so been diverted from prayer,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "until the time of prayer has passed: (TA:) by"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alxyr", "text_ar": "الخير"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is meant"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alxayol", "text_ar": "الخَيْل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Jel.)       -A3-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He became in a state of recovery from his disease."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.)       -A4-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(seed-produce)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "had, bore,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "produced, grain."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "A", "Msb", "K", "TA", "KL", "AZ"]}]}, "classical